President Obama called University of Kentucky men's basketball coach John Calipari to congratulate him and the team on their 2012 NCAA championship victory. The President praised the team for playing with class and dignity and called the game a great one to watch. He also spoke to Anthony Davis, who won the Final Four Most Outstanding Player Award. President Obama commended Coach Calipari on his first title win and expressed his excitement about congratulating the entire team in person and receiving his own Wildcats jersey at the White House.